      <name>krishg</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/162223</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I see in the following note,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;A href="https://me.sap.com/notes/2705047" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;2705047 - Roadmap for Ariba Integration Solutions - SAP for Me&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Going forward, standard integration scenarios for S/4HANA on Premise and Cloud Edition are provided based on CIG and standard APIs as part of the S/4HANA Core component. Existing Integration Scope Items may be changed to accomodate the new integration technology. &lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;CIG has 3 components ARBCI1, ARBCI2 &amp;amp; ARBCIGR.&amp;nbsp;Does it mean that we will no longer need the ARIBA add-on in S/4? If that is true, when do we expect to no longer need a add-on for ARIBA?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/spend-management-q-a/add-on-for-sap-managed-integration-gateway-for-ariba/qaq-p/13651807"/>
